QUESTION STATEMENT - 8
What are the methods for right-justifying, left-justifying, and centering a string?


What are the values of the following expressions?
'Remember, remember, the fifth of July.'.split()
'-'.join('There can only one.'.split())

SOLUTION STATEMENT - 8
'There-can-only-one.'

QUESTION STATEMENT - 9
What are the methods for right-justifying, left-justifying, and centering a string?

SOLUTION STATEMENT - 9
FOR LEFT JUSTIFYING USE ljust(), FOR RIGHT JUSTIFYING USE rjust(), AND FOR CENTERING A STRING USE center().

QUESTION STATEMENT - 10
What is the best way to remove whitespace characters from the start or end?

SOLUTION STATEMENT - 10
FOR REMOVING WHITE SPACES FROM THE START OR END WE CAN USE strip(). FOR REMOVING WHITESPACES FROM BEGINING USE "lstrip" AND FOR REMOVING WHITESPACES FROM END USE "rstrip".

